FBIS3-54240 "drnes016_l_94015" FBIS-NES-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 ISRAEL Perry Nomination Welcomed; `Fair' Approach Noted TA2501053694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 25 Jan 94 TA2501053694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] Israeli circles in Washington welcome the anticipated appointment of Dr. William Perry as the next U.S. secretary of defense. President Clinton announced Dr. Perry's nomination yesterday, but it still requires congressional approval. The Israeli sources said that William Perry has evinced an extremely fair and professional attitude in all contacts with him over the last year in his capacity as deputy secretary of defense.
